chapter.para:
The &REST-API; specification defines annotations @PathParam, @QueryParam,
@FormParam, @CookieParam, @HeaderParam and @MatrixParam.  Each annontation
requires a parameter name.  RESTEasy provides a parallel set of annotations,
@PathParam,
@QueryParam,
@FormParam,
@CookieParam,
@HeaderParam
and @MatrixParam
which do not require a parameter name.   To use this RESTEasy feature, replace the
annotation's package name, jakarta.ws.rs with,
org.jboss.resteasy.annotations.jaxrs.

chapter.programlisting:
import org.jboss.resteasy.annotations.jaxrs.*;

@Path("/library")
public class Library {

   @GET
   @Path("/book/{isbn}")
   public String getBook(@PathParam String isbn) {
      // search my database and get a string representation and return it
   }
}

import org.jboss.resteasy.annotations.jaxrs.*;

@Path("/library")
public class Library {

   @GET
   @Path("/book/{isbn}")
   public String getBook(@PathParam("isbn") String id) {
      // search my database and get a string representation and return it
   }
}
